item.title: About Me
item.description: I’m a “DevOps” Engineer. I like casual birdwatching in my local wetlands, and enjoy cooking, reading and swimming. I studied history at Monash and have an interest in historical modes of production and transitory modes of production in particular. I worked as a swimming instructor previously but re-skilled as a software engineer following a spinal injury. I am interested in projects, communities and programs that increase accessability in tech, including how we work in tech.
